WEBVTT

1
00:00:12.458 --> 00:00:15.708
-Heli 30. here U05.
-Heli 30 answers.

2
00:00:15.791 --> 00:00:19.583
A car that resembles the getaway vehicle
from last week.

3
00:00:19.666 --> 00:00:23.041
Blue Ford Taunus.
License plate November Viktor 34550.

4
00:00:23.125 --> 00:00:25.500
We have lost visual contact.

5
00:00:25.583 --> 00:00:27.250
Flying towards Marienlyst.

6
00:00:27.333 --> 00:00:29.541
We are looking for the car.

7
00:00:29.625 --> 00:00:31.625
Understood. We're going there.

8
00:00:41.708 --> 00:00:42.708
Thank you.

9
00:00:53.750 --> 00:00:54.750
Hi. boss.

10
00:00:59.541 --> 00:01:00.458
Where?

11
00:01:00.541 --> 00:01:03.333
Heli 30.
To the east on Marienlyst-Straße.

12
00:01:03.416 --> 00:01:04.958
He has seen us.

13
00:01:05.041 --> 00:01:06.208
He gets faster.

14
00:01:10.625 --> 00:01:11.958
-Hi. Tom.
-In a hurry?

15
00:01:12.041 --> 00:01:14.750
The getaway car from the robbery
has been spotted.

16
00:01:14.833 --> 00:01:16.583
See you later?

17
00:01:16.666 --> 00:01:17.500
I'm calling.

18
00:01:21.500 --> 00:01:24.250
-Harry. wait!
-U05 to all units.

19
00:01:24.333 --> 00:01:29.416
Looking for a blue Ford Taunus.
License plate November Viktor 34550.

20
00:01:29.500 --> 00:01:31.916
Bravo 41. we are on our way.

21
00:01:41.625 --> 00:01:45.166
Bravo 42. we're here.
Heading for Majorstukrysset.

22
00:01:58.333 --> 00:02:00.333
Slowly! Take it easy!

23
00:03:05.916 --> 00:03:08.000
Ten o'clock. That's the news.

24
00:03:08.083 --> 00:03:11.541
More people are demanding
that the police carry weapons.

25
00:03:11.625 --> 00:03:14.875
as Oslo now has more illegal weapons
than ever before.

26
00:03:14.958 --> 00:03:19.791
And it seems that a gang conflict
is escalating in the suburbs.

27
00:03:19.875 --> 00:03:24.125
More news:
The heatwave in Oslo continues.

28
00:03:24.208 --> 00:03:27.625
Yesterday it was over 31 degrees.

29
00:04:13.083 --> 00:04:14.583
-Helge?
-Yes?

30
00:04:15.166 --> 00:04:18.541
"The person with the highest authority
opens the safe

31
00:04:18.625 --> 00:04:22.750
and puts the money in the black bag.
She has 30 seconds.

32
00:04:22.833 --> 00:04:26.166
If it takes longer.
the person reading this will be shot."

33
00:04:30.916 --> 00:04:32.083
-27...
-Yes...

34
00:04:32.166 --> 00:04:33.708
-26...
-Wait.

35
00:04:36.625 --> 00:04:39.041
-Another 20 seconds.
-Yes. wait. I have to...

36
00:04:41.625 --> 00:04:42.791
Seventeen...

37
00:04:43.375 --> 00:04:45.458
The green ribbon. Helge.

38
00:04:47.125 --> 00:04:48.916
Just a moment.

39
00:04:49.500 --> 00:04:50.333
Seven.

40
00:04:51.583 --> 00:04:52.708
Five.

41
00:04:57.500 --> 00:05:00.416
-Two. Helge!
-Yes! Listen. I have to...

42
00:05:07.625 --> 00:05:11.000
-I have to open the other lock.
-Two. Helge!

43
00:05:11.083 --> 00:05:13.000
-Two. Helge!
-Yes!

44
00:05:24.041 --> 00:05:25.458
Here.

45
00:05:28.666 --> 00:05:30.583
Six seconds too long.

46
00:05:55.791 --> 00:05:56.750
Harry?

47
00:06:01.791 --> 00:06:03.000
Harry?

48
00:06:06.250 --> 00:06:08.958
-What the hell are you doing?
-I'm working. boss.

49
00:06:11.333 --> 00:06:14.375
The bank robbery happened
more than five years ago.

50
00:06:14.458 --> 00:06:15.291
And?

51
00:06:15.375 --> 00:06:19.000
It doesn't help anyone to reopen the case.
especially not you.

52
00:06:20.000 --> 00:06:21.000
Ok.

53
00:06:22.375 --> 00:06:24.791
Ellen? I need to know people.

54
00:06:25.916 --> 00:06:28.291
Come. The biometrics expert is here.

55
00:06:28.916 --> 00:06:31.500
The one borrowed
from the forensics department in Stockholm.

56
00:06:31.583 --> 00:06:33.166
Take care of it.

57
00:06:33.250 --> 00:06:35.416
-Me?
-I told you.

58
00:06:35.500 --> 00:06:38.250
I thought you were joking.
I don't have any...

59
00:06:38.333 --> 00:06:41.458
Knowledge of human nature?
Social competence? Leadership qualities?

60
00:06:42.041 --> 00:06:44.625
Can you pull yourself together?

61
00:06:44.708 --> 00:06:47.541
Try to get along with normal people.

62
00:06:49.125 --> 00:06:52.291
-Come on.
-Hi. Beate. Harry.

63
00:06:52.375 --> 00:06:54.500
-Lønn. Beate Lønn.
-Hi. Harry.

64
00:06:54.583 --> 00:06:56.875
-Ellen Gjelten.
-Are you Swedish?

65
00:06:58.083 --> 00:07:00.500
Yes. Uh...

66
00:07:01.041 --> 00:07:03.250
Is that a problem?

67
00:07:03.833 --> 00:07:07.750
No. I have nothing
against Sweden in general.

68
00:07:33.625 --> 00:07:34.458
Hey.

69
00:07:35.083 --> 00:07:36.791
You want to join the special unit?

70
00:07:39.166 --> 00:07:42.375
There are 270 out of 300.
Strict requirements.

71
00:07:44.333 --> 00:07:45.875
May I show you something?

72
00:07:45.958 --> 00:07:47.000
Yes. please.

73
00:07:47.083 --> 00:07:49.125
Okay. stand like you did before.

74
00:07:51.666 --> 00:07:53.208
That looks like shit.

75
00:07:54.416 --> 00:07:56.833
Right leg back. widen stance.

76
00:07:58.291 --> 00:08:01.791
Lean forward a little.
Relax your shoulders.

77
00:08:03.416 --> 00:08:05.083
-Relax.
-Yes.

78
00:08:06.291 --> 00:08:07.750
Breathe slowly.

79
00:08:09.208 --> 00:08:12.625
No thoughts. no feelings.
Only the goal exists.

80
00:08:13.791 --> 00:08:15.500
Sink into the finish.

81
00:08:16.208 --> 00:08:18.375
Breathe. Fire.

82
00:08:19.166 --> 00:08:20.000
Fire.

83
00:08:20.791 --> 00:08:21.791
Fire.

84
00:08:22.458 --> 00:08:23.625
Fire.

85
00:08:23.708 --> 00:08:25.166
Put the gun down.

86
00:08:27.166 --> 00:08:29.250
Look. You can do it.

87
00:08:30.583 --> 00:08:32.000
I can help you.

88
00:08:32.083 --> 00:08:33.875
TOM WAALER
POLICE OFFICER

89
00:08:35.750 --> 00:08:38.416
This is a Ceska Zbrojovka.

90
00:08:38.500 --> 00:08:42.916
Rarely in Oslo. but the drug squad
confiscated one yesterday.

91
00:08:43.000 --> 00:08:46.208
They found them during a raid
in a garage.

92
00:08:46.291 --> 00:08:47.791
Belongs to Sverre Olsen.

93
00:08:47.875 --> 00:08:50.958
A drug dealer.
but he probably also sells weapons.

94
00:08:51.041 --> 00:08:53.333
He committed two bank robberies.

95
00:08:54.291 --> 00:08:57.333
So you think Olsen is the bank robber?

96
00:08:57.416 --> 00:09:00.166
Nobody heard about a Ceska
before the robbery.

97
00:09:00.250 --> 00:09:02.458
Either the robber is Olsen.

98
00:09:03.125 --> 00:09:05.500
or he sold the Ceska to him.

99
00:09:05.583 --> 00:09:08.875
Yes. we must find Olsen.

100
00:09:08.958 --> 00:09:11.541
Do you need someone with people skills?

101
00:09:12.041 --> 00:09:12.875
Yes.

102
00:09:14.333 --> 00:09:15.458
Take a look at this.

103
00:09:16.916 --> 00:09:20.916
He makes them talk so that
his voice is not identified.

104
00:09:21.000 --> 00:09:23.083
Your reaction to. What does he say?

105
00:09:27.958 --> 00:09:32.750
Looks like he's telling her
that he's going to shoot her.

106
00:09:33.250 --> 00:09:35.666
and she can't believe it.

107
00:09:35.750 --> 00:09:41.208
-It was pointless. He had the money.
-Twelve years in prison instead of 21.

108
00:09:43.333 --> 00:09:44.666
What do you think?

109
00:09:44.750 --> 00:09:50.041
The report assumed that...
It shows that he is ready to kill.

110
00:09:50.125 --> 00:09:54.916
so that the police don't chase them.
but wait for the special unit.

111
00:09:55.916 --> 00:09:57.708
Have you read the report?

112
00:09:58.791 --> 00:10:03.333
Then you know that during
during the chase one of our cars

113
00:10:03.916 --> 00:10:05.375
was involved in an accident.

114
00:10:07.000 --> 00:10:10.166
Yes. tell the DEA.
I'm going to Sverre Olsen's garage.

115
00:10:10.250 --> 00:10:13.708
Yes. but weren't you... Yes.

116
00:10:25.125 --> 00:10:27.083
Take the elevator. It's hot.

117
00:10:27.791 --> 00:10:29.791
I love the damn stairs.

118
00:10:36.833 --> 00:10:41.041
Hole ran down the stairs at 30 degrees.
Did something happen?

119
00:10:41.125 --> 00:10:45.666
He has a lead on Sverre Olsen
after the gun confiscation yesterday.

120
00:10:45.750 --> 00:10:49.958
But the drug squad has it under control.
Why is he interfering?

121
00:10:50.041 --> 00:10:51.625
You should ask him.

122
00:10:54.125 --> 00:10:56.500
Don't give up. boys.

123
00:11:21.916 --> 00:11:22.916
Hi!

124
00:11:52.916 --> 00:11:54.500
-Hey. you.
-Hi.

125
00:11:55.000 --> 00:11:56.375
You called.

126
00:11:57.083 --> 00:12:00.291
I have an appointment today
with the therapist today.

127
00:12:00.375 --> 00:12:03.166
I'll be late
for dinner with you and Oleg.

128
00:12:03.250 --> 00:12:05.541
Oh. But that's good.

129
00:12:06.208 --> 00:12:07.458
When will I see you?

130
00:12:08.041 --> 00:12:11.125
Can't you just eat?
and I'll come later?

131
00:12:11.208 --> 00:12:14.958
Yes. no problem.
Will you bring a bottle of wine?

132
00:12:16.458 --> 00:12:17.750
Yes. uh...

133
00:12:18.583 --> 00:12:20.750
Yes. are you sure? It's not...

134
00:12:20.833 --> 00:12:24.333
No. hey...
It's going to be an exercise in willpower.

135
00:12:25.083 --> 00:12:26.083
Thank you.

136
00:12:27.041 --> 00:12:28.208
I love you.

137
00:12:33.750 --> 00:12:35.291
And you love me.

138
00:12:37.916 --> 00:12:38.916
Bye bye.

139
00:12:39.708 --> 00:12:40.708
Bye bye.

140
00:12:47.333 --> 00:12:50.958
ROY KVINSVIK
RACE SPORTS

141
00:12:56.875 --> 00:12:58.041
Is he here?

142
00:12:59.083 --> 00:13:00.166
Sverre?

143
00:13:00.250 --> 00:13:01.250
Yes.

144
00:13:02.750 --> 00:13:04.166
Where else would he be?

145
00:13:05.041 --> 00:13:07.000
In the other place. I suppose.

146
00:13:10.125 --> 00:13:11.666
Where is the other place?

147
00:13:16.083 --> 00:13:17.750
Shit. the cops are here.

148
00:13:25.625 --> 00:13:26.625
Stop the car!

149
00:13:32.625 --> 00:13:33.541
Stop.

150
00:13:35.333 --> 00:13:36.500
Stop the car!

151
00:13:45.708 --> 00:13:48.000
Where is Sverre Olsen's other place?

152
00:13:48.083 --> 00:13:51.750
Don't say anything. Roy.
The police are not allowed to carry weapons.

153
00:13:51.833 --> 00:13:54.708
-He can't leave you with a...
-I know. ok?

154
00:13:54.791 --> 00:13:56.541
I say nothing.

155
00:13:57.708 --> 00:14:00.833
Three hundred?
That's enough for an extra quarter. right?

156
00:14:01.458 --> 00:14:03.666
He must not bribe you either.

157
00:14:04.708 --> 00:14:05.708
Good.

158
00:14:07.041 --> 00:14:09.750
-Five hundred?
-Shit. are you deaf?

159
00:14:10.833 --> 00:14:12.041
Stop it.

160
00:14:14.583 --> 00:14:15.666
Thousand.

161
00:14:19.333 --> 00:14:22.541
Yes... I only have 800.

162
00:14:28.166 --> 00:14:29.208
Sverre Olsen.

163
00:14:29.708 --> 00:14:31.583
No.

164
00:14:33.541 --> 00:14:35.500
Under the bridge at Schous-Platz.

165
00:14:37.625 --> 00:14:38.833
Hey!

166
00:14:39.416 --> 00:14:41.833
You're right. I'm not allowed to bribe.

167
00:14:42.625 --> 00:14:45.000
And I promised to buy wine.

168
00:15:04.625 --> 00:15:07.916
Hey. Are you looking for someone?

169
00:15:08.500 --> 00:15:10.916
-Sverre.
-He's not here today.

170
00:15:11.500 --> 00:15:13.875
But I have lots of great things.

171
00:15:14.791 --> 00:15:16.958
That's ok. It's okay.

172
00:15:24.375 --> 00:15:26.666
-He's looking for me. What now?
-Listen.

173
00:15:26.750 --> 00:15:29.666
We have a cabin in Nordmarka.

174
00:15:29.750 --> 00:15:31.958
Listen. They took the weapons.

175
00:15:32.708 --> 00:15:33.708
I need money.

176
00:15:33.791 --> 00:15:36.458
We'll cover the weapons. Stay in the hut.

177
00:15:36.541 --> 00:15:39.625
Don't talk to anyone.
until you are out of the country.

178
00:15:39.708 --> 00:15:43.000
You could be our courier.
when we need more.

179
00:15:43.083 --> 00:15:46.375
-More? Do you want to start a war?
-Yes.

180
00:15:47.500 --> 00:15:51.500
-Against whom?
-against people like you.

181
00:16:04.458 --> 00:16:05.958
Fusiform gyrus.

182
00:16:07.041 --> 00:16:09.708
The part of the brain
that recognizes faces.

183
00:16:09.791 --> 00:16:11.666
And you've always had it?

184
00:16:12.250 --> 00:16:14.833
Yes. we all have a fusiform gyrus.

185
00:16:14.916 --> 00:16:16.541
It is in the brain.

186
00:16:16.625 --> 00:16:20.000
But mine has always been
a little more developed.

187
00:16:20.083 --> 00:16:22.750
So you can put any face

188
00:16:22.833 --> 00:16:25.583
in the Swedish criminal record
recognize?

189
00:16:25.666 --> 00:16:27.541
Yes. and in Norwegian.

190
00:16:28.916 --> 00:16:31.708
I had it sent to me.
before I came here.

191
00:16:31.791 --> 00:16:34.791
There are many thousands of faces.

192
00:16:34.875 --> 00:16:38.916
-Yes. it's a bit weird.
-No!

193
00:16:39.000 --> 00:16:41.583
What is it like to work with Harry Hole?

194
00:16:43.125 --> 00:16:44.125
Harry...

195
00:16:45.041 --> 00:16:48.541
I mean...
Yes. I can probably tell you everything.

196
00:16:48.625 --> 00:16:49.958
There are rumors.

197
00:16:50.041 --> 00:16:54.000
The fact that he killed a colleague
in a car accident while drunk.

198
00:16:54.083 --> 00:16:56.625
The fact that he carries a bottle of whiskey
with him.

199
00:16:56.708 --> 00:16:59.833
to prove to himself that he doesn't drink.

200
00:17:00.333 --> 00:17:03.833
Harry is the best.
just not so good at everything else.

201
00:17:04.333 --> 00:17:05.208
He is not...

202
00:17:07.000 --> 00:17:09.958
...as interested in the limelight.
as others.

203
00:17:10.791 --> 00:17:11.875
Hi. Beate.

204
00:17:11.958 --> 00:17:14.875
-Hi.
-I've heard rumors that you're coming.

205
00:17:14.958 --> 00:17:17.708
-Crazy that we're both here.
-Crazy.

206
00:17:19.208 --> 00:17:21.833
So you know each other?

207
00:17:22.500 --> 00:17:25.166
You could say that.
Is today your first day?

208
00:17:27.416 --> 00:17:30.041
The first day at work is nerve-wracking.

209
00:17:32.333 --> 00:17:35.625
I heard that you and Harry
Sverre Olsen are investigating?

210
00:17:35.708 --> 00:17:38.083
Yes. exactly. Why?

211
00:17:38.166 --> 00:17:40.375
Let me know if you need help.

212
00:17:40.458 --> 00:17:42.583
-Thanks. I'll tell Harry.
-Ok.

213
00:17:43.250 --> 00:17:44.458
See you then.

214
00:17:48.208 --> 00:17:49.583
How do you know him?

215
00:17:49.666 --> 00:17:53.708
He was my teacher at the police academy.

216
00:17:53.791 --> 00:17:56.625
That was a few years ago.

217
00:17:57.833 --> 00:17:58.833
Everything ok?

218
00:17:59.416 --> 00:18:00.791
Yes.

219
00:18:00.875 --> 00:18:03.791
But I have to get back to work. Okay.

220
00:18:03.875 --> 00:18:05.208
-Yes. bye.
-Good-bye.

221
00:18:14.125 --> 00:18:15.583
Shit!

222
00:18:47.541 --> 00:18:49.791
Even if I could buy it.

223
00:18:51.750 --> 00:18:54.166
it's not worth as much as you think.

224
00:18:55.208 --> 00:18:56.666
But it's a diamond?

225
00:18:57.166 --> 00:18:59.666
Yes. of mediocre quality.

226
00:18:59.750 --> 00:19:02.916
The red color is caused by
uncrystallized carbon.

227
00:19:03.000 --> 00:19:05.416
which makes it less clear than one would like.

228
00:19:05.500 --> 00:19:07.458
-How much will you give me?
-Well...

229
00:19:08.208 --> 00:19:10.666
I assume you don't have a certificate?

230
00:19:12.583 --> 00:19:16.041
Good. Looks like a blood diamond.

231
00:19:16.625 --> 00:19:18.125
Are you going to buy it or not?

232
00:19:18.916 --> 00:19:20.625
No. I can't.

233
00:19:26.375 --> 00:19:27.541
PSYCHOLOGIST

234
00:19:27.625 --> 00:19:31.125
Hi. I'm Harry.
and I'm an alcoholic.

235
00:19:31.958 --> 00:19:35.375
And that was so hard
for you to say.

236
00:19:35.458 --> 00:19:37.958
that you didn't go back?

237
00:19:40.333 --> 00:19:42.083
It helps many. but...

238
00:19:42.708 --> 00:19:44.625
You'd better come here.

239
00:19:46.125 --> 00:19:47.916
We work together. so...

240
00:19:48.000 --> 00:19:49.291
Why now?

241
00:19:50.375 --> 00:19:52.666
You've been sober for a long time. haven't you?

242
00:19:54.125 --> 00:19:56.833
Yes... I met someone.

243
00:19:57.750 --> 00:19:58.875
I knew it.

244
00:20:01.166 --> 00:20:04.708
You would never buy such an expensive wine
for yourself.

245
00:20:06.208 --> 00:20:09.833
And when you came through the door.
I barely recognized you.

246
00:20:10.625 --> 00:20:13.291
"Like a normal. happy person."

247
00:20:14.666 --> 00:20:17.083
Yes. I prefer to play it safe.

248
00:20:19.666 --> 00:20:22.083
-I don't want to mess it up.
-No.

249
00:20:26.000 --> 00:20:32.333
I heard that you're watching
the videos of the bank robbery again.

250
00:20:35.833 --> 00:20:37.000
You think.

251
00:20:37.083 --> 00:20:42.625
that there would not have been an accident.
if you had solved the case faster.

252
00:20:43.208 --> 00:20:47.416
And maybe you think
that Lars would still be alive.

253
00:20:48.166 --> 00:20:50.333
It's been five years. Harry.

254
00:20:51.625 --> 00:20:53.458
You have to keep going.

255
00:20:54.000 --> 00:20:57.041
What does that have to do with
that I met someone?

256
00:20:57.125 --> 00:20:59.458
You don't want to mess it up.

257
00:21:00.125 --> 00:21:02.541
And what always screws it up for you?

258
00:21:03.541 --> 00:21:05.291
Your self-hatred.

259
00:21:06.833 --> 00:21:08.333
Is that why I drink?

260
00:21:09.750 --> 00:21:11.291
What do you think?

261
00:21:14.250 --> 00:21:15.875
I drink out of thirst.

262
00:21:16.750 --> 00:21:18.791
And I'm always thirsty.

263
00:21:19.750 --> 00:21:25.916
Two years. three months and seven days.
since I last drank.

264
00:21:26.000 --> 00:21:28.916
But I was shaking.
when I bought the wine.

265
00:21:29.000 --> 00:21:32.541
Did you come here because you think
that I have the answer?

266
00:21:33.791 --> 00:21:38.833
No. I think I want to
to hear myself say what I just said.

267
00:21:38.916 --> 00:21:40.375
Isn't that what you're there for?

268
00:21:40.458 --> 00:21:42.666
Okay. That's reassuring.

269
00:21:46.208 --> 00:21:47.750
You have five minutes left.

270
00:21:47.833 --> 00:21:51.791
If there is something
you want to ask or tell...

271
00:22:01.833 --> 00:22:03.166
-Hi.
-Hi.

272
00:22:03.250 --> 00:22:05.958
-You look good.
-Hi.

273
00:22:07.333 --> 00:22:08.291
Hi. Oleg.

274
00:22:09.291 --> 00:22:10.416
Oleg. say hi.

275
00:22:13.500 --> 00:22:14.958
-Yes...
-I don't know if...

276
00:22:15.041 --> 00:22:16.583
I can drink this.

277
00:22:16.666 --> 00:22:19.458
-What's the name of the old game. Mom?
-Tetris.

278
00:22:19.541 --> 00:22:21.083
-Tetris. right?
-Tetris.

279
00:22:21.166 --> 00:22:24.791
I told him.
that your record was 17.559 points.

280
00:22:24.875 --> 00:22:27.250
I can beat him easily. I have 18.000.

281
00:22:27.333 --> 00:22:28.916
I'll catch up. kiddo.

282
00:22:29.000 --> 00:22:30.875
We can see that. old man.

283
00:22:33.375 --> 00:22:36.208
-How's it going?
-No informant knows where he is.

284
00:22:36.291 --> 00:22:39.875
The drug squad sends recordings
of the garage.

285
00:22:39.958 --> 00:22:41.625
whether I recognize someone.

286
00:22:41.708 --> 00:22:44.000
but the quality is so bad...

287
00:22:45.458 --> 00:22:46.666
A convict.

288
00:22:47.916 --> 00:22:48.916
Drugs.

289
00:22:49.000 --> 00:22:51.333
Kvinsvik something.

290
00:22:55.833 --> 00:22:58.333
Also a convict. Drugs again.

291
00:22:59.208 --> 00:23:00.208
Ok.

292
00:23:00.750 --> 00:23:02.875
These are customers.

293
00:23:02.958 --> 00:23:05.583
They're in there for a minute or two.

294
00:23:05.666 --> 00:23:08.791
You probably don't know
where Sverre Olsen is.

295
00:23:09.416 --> 00:23:13.791
The guy is in there for 20 minutes.
He knows something.

296
00:23:16.208 --> 00:23:17.666
No. I don't think so.

297
00:23:18.666 --> 00:23:19.541
Why not?

298
00:23:19.625 --> 00:23:21.125
He would have told us.

299
00:23:23.375 --> 00:23:25.041
Can't you see who it is?

300
00:23:28.041 --> 00:23:29.916
He was worse with my ex.

301
00:23:30.000 --> 00:23:34.166
He bought Oleg a Rosenborg jersey.
and Oleg changed teams.

302
00:23:34.666 --> 00:23:36.750
He cheered on Molde instead.

303
00:23:38.750 --> 00:23:41.458
He doesn't make friends easily. so...

304
00:23:42.958 --> 00:23:44.875
He's afraid of losing me.

305
00:23:44.958 --> 00:23:49.833
He doesn't have to accept me.
If you and I...

306
00:23:50.916 --> 00:23:52.541
When we what?

307
00:23:55.333 --> 00:23:59.583
If we both carry on.

308
00:24:01.583 --> 00:24:05.875
Oleg has to decide for himself.
who I am for him or not.

309
00:24:06.625 --> 00:24:07.625
Ok?

310
00:24:09.041 --> 00:24:10.291
Ok.

311
00:24:11.166 --> 00:24:14.125
Do you know what the women
said at the station?

312
00:24:14.208 --> 00:24:16.833
No. but I don't want to know either.

313
00:24:16.916 --> 00:24:21.125
They said that no one can have Harry Hole
can have Harry Hole all to himself.

314
00:24:21.750 --> 00:24:23.958
Because he loves his freedom too much.

315
00:24:26.333 --> 00:24:29.833
-And?
-I have no interest in that.

316
00:24:30.916 --> 00:24:33.833
I want all of you. otherwise it's pointless.

317
00:24:34.958 --> 00:24:38.375
If that's a problem.
you should tell me now.

318
00:24:51.666 --> 00:24:53.000
I just have to...

319
00:24:53.833 --> 00:24:54.916
Yes. what's up?

320
00:24:56.208 --> 00:24:57.208
Yes...

321
00:24:59.208 --> 00:25:01.791
Okay. Yes. I'm on my way.

322
00:25:04.125 --> 00:25:06.625
Beate Lønn has identified Tom Waaler.

323
00:25:06.708 --> 00:25:09.750
On the surveillance videos
of Sverre Olsen's garage.

324
00:25:09.833 --> 00:25:11.625
It's Tom Waaler!

325
00:25:13.375 --> 00:25:15.291
Yes. and what does Waaler say?

326
00:25:15.875 --> 00:25:17.333
Nothing yet.

327
00:25:17.416 --> 00:25:20.166
He's not at work
and does not answer.

328
00:25:21.208 --> 00:25:24.666
I'll pick you up. We're going to his place.

329
00:25:29.250 --> 00:25:32.125
Did she say how safe she was?

330
00:25:33.083 --> 00:25:35.750
-Seventy percent.
-Ok.

331
00:25:35.833 --> 00:25:38.000
It is very specific.

332
00:25:38.083 --> 00:25:39.083
Yes. hello?

333
00:25:39.166 --> 00:25:41.916
This is Ellen Gjelten.
Can we come in?

334
00:25:42.583 --> 00:25:44.958
Is it important? I am busy.

335
00:25:45.458 --> 00:25:46.875
Takes only five minutes.

336
00:25:55.541 --> 00:25:57.916
See you later. I'm sorry.

337
00:25:58.000 --> 00:25:59.000
Hi.

338
00:26:08.000 --> 00:26:11.833
-Not bad for a police salary.
-I inherited well.

339
00:26:11.916 --> 00:26:13.375
What do you want?

340
00:26:13.458 --> 00:26:16.416
You had contact with Sverre Olsen.

341
00:26:17.083 --> 00:26:19.000
The case is in the hands of the drug squad.

342
00:26:19.083 --> 00:26:20.875
Yes. exactly.

343
00:26:21.791 --> 00:26:25.375
But why didn't you tell us?

344
00:26:28.208 --> 00:26:29.375
What is that?

345
00:26:29.458 --> 00:26:30.625
This is you.

346
00:26:31.750 --> 00:26:32.916
What?

347
00:26:33.000 --> 00:26:35.583
-According to the analysis. that's you.
-What analysis?

348
00:26:36.375 --> 00:26:39.583
What did you do?
Why did you keep it a secret?

349
00:26:39.666 --> 00:26:40.958
What are you doing?

350
00:26:42.291 --> 00:26:44.125
Are you saying it's not you?

351
00:26:45.500 --> 00:26:47.541
You accuse a colleague.

352
00:26:47.625 --> 00:26:52.375
because you have photos from software
that delivers incorrect results 90% of the time.

353
00:26:52.458 --> 00:26:55.708
This is not software. Tom.

354
00:26:55.791 --> 00:26:57.041
And what...

355
00:26:59.125 --> 00:27:03.291
Did Beate Lønn say that she sees things
that others don't see?

356
00:27:03.375 --> 00:27:06.583
Beate Lønn sees things.
that others do not see.

357
00:27:08.250 --> 00:27:12.666
We had a relationship.
that didn't end the way she wanted it to.

358
00:27:14.625 --> 00:27:15.750
Really?

359
00:27:17.291 --> 00:27:20.458
And that's why you think
she's lying now. right?

360
00:27:20.541 --> 00:27:22.375
It wouldn't be the first time.

361
00:27:22.458 --> 00:27:26.541
If we check where you were
when the pictures were taken...

362
00:27:31.000 --> 00:27:34.166
I'm either here or at work.

363
00:27:44.416 --> 00:27:46.625
Are Lucas and the others on vacation?

364
00:27:47.375 --> 00:27:48.375
I don't know.

365
00:27:51.083 --> 00:27:52.541
Is the guy coming back?

366
00:27:53.041 --> 00:27:54.458
Say his name.

367
00:27:56.291 --> 00:28:00.416
I don't know.
It depends on how late it gets.

368
00:28:00.916 --> 00:28:02.375
Does he have the keys?

369
00:28:02.958 --> 00:28:04.041
No.

370
00:28:04.791 --> 00:28:08.458
I don't like it when he sleeps here.
He can sleep at home.

371
00:28:10.458 --> 00:28:11.500
Ok.

372
00:28:13.416 --> 00:28:14.250
Oleg?

373
00:28:15.458 --> 00:28:18.416
-It's ok.
-Thank you.

374
00:28:18.500 --> 00:28:20.333
It must be Waaler.

375
00:28:21.125 --> 00:28:26.291
I'm not saying that Beate Lønn is lying.
but 70%? Two out of three.

376
00:28:28.250 --> 00:28:30.291
If they have a history.

377
00:28:30.375 --> 00:28:32.791
he naturally pops up in her head.

378
00:28:32.875 --> 00:28:36.958
No. but I trust Beate Lønn
more than Tom Waaler.

379
00:28:38.250 --> 00:28:40.416
How did it go with the therapist?

380
00:28:40.500 --> 00:28:43.416
Aune thinks I have commitment issues.

381
00:28:43.500 --> 00:28:46.458
-Oh. that's what he says. is it?
-Yes.

382
00:28:46.541 --> 00:28:48.291
He says it's because I...

383
00:28:49.458 --> 00:28:52.375
...lost my mother.
when I was little. and because...

384
00:28:53.208 --> 00:28:59.333
...my first girlfriend killed herself.
And then... Yes. the car accident.

385
00:29:01.291 --> 00:29:04.250
Then I prefer to
to be alone.

386
00:29:04.875 --> 00:29:07.875
And then I decide to numb myself.

387
00:29:10.125 --> 00:29:11.625
Psychologist gobbledygook.

388
00:29:13.291 --> 00:29:17.833
Oh God. but that's the way it is. Harry.
Love. Bloody hell.

389
00:29:17.916 --> 00:29:21.333
Sometimes it's like fate.
that it goes down the drain.

390
00:29:21.416 --> 00:29:24.375
So one hopes that the end will come soon.

391
00:29:24.458 --> 00:29:27.125
so that you can get it over with.

392
00:29:28.666 --> 00:29:29.833
Is it over?

393
00:29:33.833 --> 00:29:38.166
He was a bastard. like you said.
I'm fine. it's just...

394
00:29:38.250 --> 00:29:41.333
What did you do?
Thrown another chair?

395
00:29:42.583 --> 00:29:44.875
No. I didn't. Not this time.

396
00:29:44.958 --> 00:29:47.458
Even if he deserved it this time.

397
00:29:49.000 --> 00:29:52.125
Fortunately. we humans can
get through something like this.

398
00:29:52.208 --> 00:29:54.916
Despite everything. We survive.

399
00:29:55.500 --> 00:29:56.708
No. we do not.

400
00:29:57.750 --> 00:30:01.416
We simply decay
a little slower or a little faster.

401
00:30:05.541 --> 00:30:07.083
You are so broken.

402
00:30:13.166 --> 00:30:15.541
See you on Sunday Rakel Fauke

403
00:30:15.625 --> 00:30:18.291
at least three times that you love her.

404
00:30:18.375 --> 00:30:19.791
Can you do that?

405
00:30:20.500 --> 00:30:21.833
Have a nice sample.

406
00:30:22.750 --> 00:30:24.333
Yes. I love you too.

407
00:30:24.416 --> 00:30:25.500
-Bye.
-Bye.

408
00:30:25.583 --> 00:30:28.208
Three times. Hole! Three times!

409
00:31:26.041 --> 00:31:28.750
INVESTIGATION REPORT
BANK ROBBERY IN MAJORSTUA

410
00:31:54.500 --> 00:31:56.625
I would like to introduce myself.

411
00:31:57.625 --> 00:32:01.541
I am the creature.
which. according to your hope. does not exist.

412
00:32:02.166 --> 00:32:06.625
I am the one
who crawls out from under your bed.

413
00:32:07.250 --> 00:32:09.875
The one who sits on your chest.

414
00:32:09.958 --> 00:32:12.500
puts the bridle in your mouth

415
00:32:13.500 --> 00:32:14.958
and rides you.

416
00:32:15.458 --> 00:32:18.625
I'll ride you all the way to hell.

417
00:32:28.583 --> 00:32:30.416
-Hi. boss. What's up?
-Hi. Boris.

418
00:32:30.500 --> 00:32:32.875
I'd like a quarter or two.

419
00:32:33.958 --> 00:32:36.333
Can you take something from your stash?

420
00:32:36.875 --> 00:32:41.791
-They searched the garage.
-Crap. Where can I get powder now?

421
00:32:41.875 --> 00:32:46.875
No. I'll be back soon.
Don't look for a new supplier yet.

422
00:32:47.583 --> 00:32:50.083
I'll send you a place. Come quickly.

423
00:32:50.166 --> 00:32:51.000
Yes. ok.

424
00:32:51.083 --> 00:32:54.041
Not a word about my whereabouts. ok?

425
00:32:54.125 --> 00:32:56.666
What the hell? It's in the middle of the forest!

426
00:32:57.458 --> 00:32:59.875
-Do you have the money?
-I'll pay later.

427
00:32:59.958 --> 00:33:01.166
No.

428
00:33:02.291 --> 00:33:03.458
No?

429
00:33:03.541 --> 00:33:07.125
Hey. I got this from you.
Call me when you have the money.

430
00:33:07.208 --> 00:33:09.000
Boris? Boris...

431
00:33:10.666 --> 00:33:12.250
Bloody hell!

432
00:33:22.000 --> 00:33:23.416
Thanks for coming along.

433
00:33:23.500 --> 00:33:24.958
No problem.

434
00:33:25.041 --> 00:33:29.583
No. I know.
that's not your thing.

435
00:33:30.166 --> 00:33:35.958
What. Saturday in the park?
It doesn't get any better than this.

436
00:33:37.583 --> 00:33:39.125
We are delighted.

437
00:33:40.375 --> 00:33:43.750
-Would anyone like an ice cream?
-Yes.

438
00:33:43.833 --> 00:33:46.458
-I can get it.
-No. I'll get it.

439
00:33:47.625 --> 00:33:51.875
I'm leaving.
You can try to talk to each other.

440
00:33:53.625 --> 00:33:54.791
This is how you do it.

441
00:33:58.208 --> 00:33:59.625
His name is Boris Koupich.

442
00:33:59.708 --> 00:34:02.291
At least the drug squad knows.

443
00:34:02.375 --> 00:34:06.208
that he sold drugs
for Sverre Olsen.

444
00:34:06.750 --> 00:34:10.083
I'll send you a photo.
so you can see what it looks like.

445
00:34:10.166 --> 00:34:13.083
You owe me one.

446
00:34:13.166 --> 00:34:16.375
And the repair of the chair.
that you threw.

447
00:34:21.000 --> 00:34:23.791
Boris Koupich? Where is Sverre Olsen?

448
00:34:23.875 --> 00:34:24.958
Stop!

449
00:34:25.916 --> 00:34:27.750
Just tell me where he is.

450
00:34:32.541 --> 00:34:35.541
PLAYER: OLEG_7
POINTS: 1457

451
00:34:39.750 --> 00:34:42.166
What did mom mean. it's not your thing?

452
00:34:44.166 --> 00:34:46.750
Too much sun and too much noise.

453
00:34:47.791 --> 00:34:49.166
Far too many people.

454
00:34:58.291 --> 00:35:00.625
Have you been on the diving platform?

455
00:35:05.166 --> 00:35:06.625
I don't like heights.

456
00:35:14.083 --> 00:35:15.375
Are you freezing?

457
00:35:18.333 --> 00:35:19.375
Huh?

458
00:35:21.208 --> 00:35:24.750
If you want to jump. stand on the edge.

459
00:35:24.833 --> 00:35:27.541
and you can't move.

460
00:35:28.375 --> 00:35:29.666
How do you know about it?

461
00:35:30.958 --> 00:35:32.750
I froze too.

462
00:35:34.708 --> 00:35:36.333
Before you wanted to jump?

463
00:35:36.416 --> 00:35:39.750
No. not that.

464
00:35:41.000 --> 00:35:43.250
I wanted to save my sister.

465
00:35:48.833 --> 00:35:49.916
How?

466
00:35:52.708 --> 00:35:57.166
I think I was twelve.
We took the elevator.

467
00:35:58.875 --> 00:36:03.041
And her hair got caught
between the wall and the elevator.

468
00:36:05.041 --> 00:36:06.458
And you froze?

469
00:36:08.666 --> 00:36:09.625
Yes.

470
00:36:10.750 --> 00:36:12.291
Was she ok?

471
00:36:13.541 --> 00:36:17.875
She was doing well. losing hair and...

472
00:36:17.958 --> 00:36:20.541
It bled. but it has healed.

473
00:36:21.833 --> 00:36:22.958
What about you?

474
00:36:26.958 --> 00:36:28.750
I can't take elevators.

475
00:36:29.416 --> 00:36:31.625
-Really not?
-No.

476
00:36:36.041 --> 00:36:37.041
Listen.

477
00:36:37.750 --> 00:36:42.958
If you jump from the 10-meter tower.
I'll take the elevator to the 10th floor.

478
00:36:48.375 --> 00:36:49.500
Never.

479
00:36:56.333 --> 00:36:59.208
-Yes. what's up?
-I know where Sverre Olsen is.

480
00:37:00.541 --> 00:37:04.875
And now I have a location
for a hut in Nordmarka.

481
00:37:06.625 --> 00:37:08.250
Are you coming or what?

482
00:37:09.416 --> 00:37:10.833
Yes. wait. I...

483
00:37:11.500 --> 00:37:15.250
The Frogner bath?
You're a family man today!

484
00:37:15.333 --> 00:37:18.875
-Yes. but I'm talking to...
-No. hey. my darling.

485
00:37:18.958 --> 00:37:23.208
Take advantage of the only opportunity
that people like us get. Okay?

486
00:37:23.291 --> 00:37:26.458
-I'm going to the location.
-Good. but hey...

487
00:37:26.541 --> 00:37:30.833
-Don't do anything... I mean. no...
-No confrontation. no arrests.

488
00:37:30.916 --> 00:37:33.416
I'll check.
whether Boris was telling the truth.

489
00:37:33.500 --> 00:37:36.958
If Olsen is there.
I'll call the guys with the guns.

490
00:37:37.041 --> 00:37:40.583
-Call the special unit. and then me.
-Yes. I will.

491
00:37:41.166 --> 00:37:42.125
Good.

492
00:37:42.833 --> 00:37:44.708
-Here.
-Thank you.

493
00:37:46.291 --> 00:37:48.750
What did you talk about?

494
00:37:50.041 --> 00:37:52.625
-The weather.
-About the weather?

495
00:37:52.708 --> 00:37:55.375
-Yes. it's damn beautiful.
-Oleg...

496
00:37:55.958 --> 00:37:58.291
-Sorry.
-But it's damn beautiful.

497
00:38:14.625 --> 00:38:15.666
Olsen?

498
00:38:16.625 --> 00:38:17.708
I need money.

499
00:38:19.250 --> 00:38:22.333
-Or I say everything.
-Who?

500
00:38:23.375 --> 00:38:24.791
The police. of course.

501
00:38:26.833 --> 00:38:29.416
And you think they'll give you money?

502
00:38:32.750 --> 00:38:33.916
Maybe not.

503
00:38:37.208 --> 00:38:40.541
But they reduce my sentence
to a few months.

504
00:38:43.375 --> 00:38:45.125
Maybe I'll do it.

505
00:38:46.791 --> 00:38:48.041
Too bad for you.

506
00:38:49.750 --> 00:38:52.208
Arms dealing brings four years. right?

507
00:38:55.083 --> 00:38:56.291
And everything else.

508
00:39:00.166 --> 00:39:01.958
I'll think about it. Olsen.

509
00:39:10.750 --> 00:39:13.833
Mom. I don't want
be called a sissy.

510
00:39:13.916 --> 00:39:17.083
You're sure to make it
by the end of the summer.

511
00:39:17.166 --> 00:39:19.958
He jumps off the 10-meter tower once. doesn't he?

512
00:39:20.041 --> 00:39:22.083
No. I don't think so.

513
00:39:24.375 --> 00:39:28.916
-What do you mean?
-Maybe five. but not ten.

514
00:39:29.000 --> 00:39:30.041
Why not?

515
00:39:31.000 --> 00:39:32.708
Because it's high up.

516
00:39:33.291 --> 00:39:36.250
-Did you jump from the 10-meter tower?
-No.

517
00:39:38.166 --> 00:39:40.541
I once jumped from a height of seven meters...

518
00:39:42.416 --> 00:39:43.416
Really.

519
00:39:44.875 --> 00:39:45.875
When?

520
00:39:45.958 --> 00:39:46.958
Hi.

521
00:39:47.666 --> 00:39:49.791
When I was your age.

522
00:39:50.833 --> 00:39:53.333
I snuck in.
when it was closed.

523
00:39:53.416 --> 00:39:54.791
Why?

524
00:39:54.875 --> 00:39:59.125
So no one could see me.
when I pinched and went downstairs.

525
00:40:01.250 --> 00:40:03.583
No. that's all right. Okay.

526
00:40:04.291 --> 00:40:08.500
That was Eric. He has a contract.
that he needs help with.

527
00:40:08.583 --> 00:40:12.916
It has to be submitted by Monday.
I have to do it. Is that ok?

528
00:40:13.458 --> 00:40:14.416
Sure.

529
00:40:14.916 --> 00:40:17.791
-Do something.
-We find a job.

530
00:40:17.875 --> 00:40:20.458
-Safe?
-Yes. we should be able to manage that.

531
00:40:20.541 --> 00:40:21.375
Thank you.

532
00:40:22.208 --> 00:40:25.791
...turn me around
I dance. hop and jump for you

533
00:40:25.875 --> 00:40:31.375
I wish you all the best from the bottom of my heart
And tell me. what else do you want?

534
00:40:31.458 --> 00:40:34.958
Congratulations

535
00:40:37.041 --> 00:40:40.958
He offered me the position
deputy chief of police.

536
00:40:41.041 --> 00:40:42.250
Wow. Congratulations.

537
00:40:43.291 --> 00:40:46.125
I recommend you
as head of the criminal investigation department.

538
00:40:46.708 --> 00:40:49.333
-Me?
-Yes. the seats change.

539
00:40:50.166 --> 00:40:53.583
-Yes. chief of the criminal investigation department.
-Here he is. Chief of Police.

540
00:40:53.666 --> 00:40:55.208
Happy birthday to you.

541
00:40:57.000 --> 00:40:59.041
-Hi.
-Hi.

542
00:41:00.000 --> 00:41:05.083
Is there someone in your department
who could take over your position?

543
00:41:05.166 --> 00:41:08.333
Sure. Ellen Gjelten
has the best leadership qualities.

544
00:41:08.958 --> 00:41:13.541
She is good with people.
has guts and thinks unconventionally.

545
00:41:14.125 --> 00:41:14.958
But?

546
00:41:15.625 --> 00:41:18.125
Tom Waaler is the most ambitious.

547
00:41:18.208 --> 00:41:20.833
He has the highest clearance rate
after Hole.

548
00:41:22.041 --> 00:41:23.583
Tell me about Waaler.

549
00:41:24.666 --> 00:41:29.250
The drug squad has borrowed it for a case
from Interpol in Brussels.

550
00:41:29.333 --> 00:41:30.958
He likes it here.

551
00:41:31.041 --> 00:41:33.916
He completed the authorization course
at the police academy

552
00:41:34.000 --> 00:41:36.458
and then he switched to us. Smart. tough.

553
00:41:36.541 --> 00:41:41.375
He knows the system and knows
how to find your way around it.

554
00:41:41.458 --> 00:41:44.708
But you don't want Harry Hole?

555
00:41:46.750 --> 00:41:49.833
No. I like Harry.
It's nothing like that. but...

556
00:41:49.916 --> 00:41:52.708
It would be best
if he only does one thing.

557
00:41:53.250 --> 00:41:55.916
He doesn't always stick to the rules.

558
00:41:56.000 --> 00:42:00.500
-Won't we get caught either?
-No. we won't. Up you go.

559
00:42:31.250 --> 00:42:32.291
Shit.

560
00:42:33.750 --> 00:42:36.125
The Lotus was parked at police headquarters.

561
00:42:37.250 --> 00:42:40.000
Organized crime. Isaksson. right?

562
00:42:40.083 --> 00:42:43.791
You have a good memory. Waaler.
What are you doing here?

563
00:42:45.083 --> 00:42:46.583
We received a tip.

564
00:42:46.666 --> 00:42:49.541
We are looking for one.
who could be in a hut.

565
00:42:50.166 --> 00:42:53.458
Do you need help?
I know the place inside out.

566
00:42:53.541 --> 00:42:57.958
No. pure formality.
It's logical that he's here.

567
00:42:58.041 --> 00:42:59.166
Ok.

568
00:42:59.250 --> 00:43:00.375
Beautiful leggings.

569
00:43:03.583 --> 00:43:04.875
Thank you.

570
00:43:07.458 --> 00:43:09.666
Okay. see you around.

571
00:43:34.166 --> 00:43:35.666
Ok.

572
00:43:41.041 --> 00:43:44.833
Seven meters feels higher than you would think.
than you would think.

573
00:43:46.083 --> 00:43:50.125
-Sure it's deep enough?
-Only one way to find out.

574
00:44:02.416 --> 00:44:03.791
It is deep enough.

575
00:44:19.166 --> 00:44:21.166
Yes. mine was better than yours.

576
00:44:21.250 --> 00:44:24.958
No. The point is
that the water splashes.

577
00:44:25.041 --> 00:44:26.625
I am the champion here.

578
00:44:26.708 --> 00:44:29.250
Unless you jump from the 10-meter tower.
Next year.

579
00:44:37.500 --> 00:44:38.916
Ok.

580
00:44:40.791 --> 00:44:41.833
Ok.

581
00:44:46.500 --> 00:44:47.666
The Prince.

582
00:44:51.291 --> 00:44:52.333
Hello. Sverre.

583
00:44:57.375 --> 00:44:58.500
Do you have any coffee?

584
00:45:00.833 --> 00:45:02.666
Delta. Falkeid on the line.

585
00:45:03.666 --> 00:45:04.500
Hello?

586
00:45:05.708 --> 00:45:09.125
-I hope you have something for me.
-Of course.

587
00:45:22.666 --> 00:45:23.875
Just a moment.

588
00:45:23.958 --> 00:45:25.250
Here.

589
00:45:27.375 --> 00:45:28.458
Here.

590
00:45:34.458 --> 00:45:36.708
Hi. this is Harry. What's up?

591
00:46:18.375 --> 00:46:19.416
Should I do it?

592
00:46:20.375 --> 00:46:24.666
I don't really want to
lose to a kid. so...

593
00:46:25.208 --> 00:46:29.375
I'll give you 50 crowns.
if we postpone it until next year.

594
00:46:33.375 --> 00:46:37.791
-Hundred.
-No. forget it. I'm a policeman.

595
00:46:52.416 --> 00:46:54.791
I turn around in three seconds.

596
00:46:54.875 --> 00:46:57.666
It doesn't count.
if you don't have a witness.

597
00:47:00.291 --> 00:47:01.250
Three.

598
00:47:01.791 --> 00:47:02.875
Two.

599
00:47:04.375 --> 00:47:05.333
One.

600
00:47:21.333 --> 00:47:24.625
You loser.
Now you have to take the elevator.

601
00:47:25.458 --> 00:47:29.333
-I will. Do you want to be a witness?
-I definitely do.

602
00:47:29.916 --> 00:47:31.000
Yes. what's up?

603
00:47:31.083 --> 00:47:33.750
Hey. you. We're done. What are you doing?

604
00:47:33.833 --> 00:47:36.166
-We went fishing.
-Ok.

605
00:47:37.833 --> 00:47:40.291
-I'll be right there.
-We're almost finished.

606
00:47:42.125 --> 00:47:45.166
That's great. You're damn good.

607
00:47:45.791 --> 00:47:48.875
-Thank you.
-I'm afraid I ruined your Saturday.

608
00:47:48.958 --> 00:47:52.625
-Can I buy you a drink?
-All right. Some other time.

609
00:47:53.333 --> 00:47:54.708
Another time.

610
00:48:20.333 --> 00:48:23.041
Hi. this is Ellen's mailbox. What's up?

611
00:48:30.916 --> 00:48:32.375
Ok...

612
00:48:40.750 --> 00:48:42.250
What is the name of the song?

613
00:48:43.166 --> 00:48:46.875
This is the Ramones.
"I Wanna Be Sedated."

614
00:48:48.291 --> 00:48:50.250
-Have you heard of it?
-No.

615
00:48:50.916 --> 00:48:53.583
Hi. this is Ellen's mailbox. What...

616
00:48:55.416 --> 00:48:57.125
What are you going to tell mom?

617
00:49:00.333 --> 00:49:02.041
That we didn't catch any fish.

618
00:49:03.041 --> 00:49:04.291
That is a lie.

619
00:49:04.958 --> 00:49:05.958
Oh?

620
00:49:06.458 --> 00:49:07.875
Did you catch anything?

621
00:49:09.916 --> 00:49:10.750
No.

622
00:49:11.250 --> 00:49:13.875
Hi. this is Ellen's mailbox. What...

623
00:49:34.500 --> 00:49:36.000
No...

624
00:49:51.750 --> 00:49:55.208
Tom? Tom. what are you doing?

625
00:50:00.875 --> 00:50:03.333
Tom. what are you doing?

626
00:50:04.708 --> 00:50:07.416
-Talk to me.
-What were you doing in the forest?

627
00:50:10.333 --> 00:50:11.333
Shit!

628
00:50:18.958 --> 00:50:21.166
-Thank you.
-Yes. thank you.

629
00:50:23.916 --> 00:50:25.750
-Hi. Mom.
-Hi! Did you have fun?

630
00:50:25.833 --> 00:50:27.583
-Yes.
-Yes? Good.

631
00:50:29.625 --> 00:50:31.208
-Yes?
-Hi. boss. it's me.

632
00:50:31.291 --> 00:50:33.583
I try to reach Ellen.

633
00:50:33.666 --> 00:50:37.375
She is alone
on a potentially dangerous mission.

634
00:50:37.458 --> 00:50:39.083
I don't know where she is.

635
00:50:39.166 --> 00:50:42.958
-Alone? Damn it. Harry...
-I know it's my responsibility.

636
00:50:43.041 --> 00:50:45.750
Could you locate her cell phone?

637
00:50:47.125 --> 00:50:50.000
-Are you worried?
-Yes. always. boss.

638
00:50:51.791 --> 00:50:53.041
Ok. will do.

639
00:51:01.500 --> 00:51:06.000
Tom. nothing has happened yet.
I promise.

640
00:51:11.458 --> 00:51:15.250
Tom. listen to me.
I'll keep my mouth shut. I promise.

641
00:51:15.333 --> 00:51:18.291
He too. He bleeds to death.
We blame him.

642
00:51:18.375 --> 00:51:22.041
Please. Hey. it's not you.
It's not you.

643
00:51:22.541 --> 00:51:26.166
You're a good man.
I'll keep my mouth shut. I promise.

644
00:51:26.250 --> 00:51:27.750
I don't want that.

645
00:51:27.833 --> 00:51:30.041
No. you haven't done anything yet.

646
00:51:30.666 --> 00:51:32.833
Tom. you haven't done anything yet.

647
00:51:32.916 --> 00:51:33.958
I'm sorry.

648
00:51:34.041 --> 00:51:37.250
No. it's all right.
He won't say anything and I'll...

649
00:51:41.916 --> 00:51:42.916
Ellen.

650
00:51:45.416 --> 00:51:46.833
Damn.

651
00:51:48.500 --> 00:51:51.041
Here. Let me see.

652
00:52:03.166 --> 00:52:07.041
Now you can hold them. Like this.

653
00:52:09.625 --> 00:52:10.458
So.

654
00:52:10.541 --> 00:52:11.791
No!

655
00:52:11.875 --> 00:52:15.250
Sverre? Point the gun at Ellen.

656
00:52:15.833 --> 00:52:17.500
And then you shoot them.

657
00:52:18.333 --> 00:52:19.541
Targets on them.

658
00:52:19.625 --> 00:52:23.041
A little higher. And then you pull the trigger.

659
00:52:24.291 --> 00:52:25.666
Pull the trigger.

660
00:52:26.291 --> 00:52:29.250
-One. two. three.
-No...

661
00:52:32.416 --> 00:52:35.375
-Can't you do that?
-Try again.

662
00:52:35.875 --> 00:52:38.875
Then I know
that I can trust you. Okay?

663
00:52:38.958 --> 00:52:39.791
Ok.

664
00:52:39.875 --> 00:52:42.666
One more time. One. two...

665
00:52:47.125 --> 00:52:48.208
Good.

666
00:53:01.916 --> 00:53:03.583
Police operations center.

667
00:53:03.666 --> 00:53:07.000
Yes. hello? Commissioner Tom Waaler.

668
00:53:07.666 --> 00:53:09.333
A colleague was killed.

669
00:53:09.416 --> 00:53:11.708
The perpetrator too.
I had to shoot in self-defense.

670
00:53:11.791 --> 00:53:14.291
I'm in a cabin in Nordmarka.

671
00:53:14.375 --> 00:53:16.208
I am sending coordinates.

672
00:53:18.166 --> 00:53:20.166
Forensics must come here.

673
00:53:41.083 --> 00:53:42.083
Hi. Harry.

674
00:53:43.291 --> 00:53:46.083
-What is Waaler doing here?
-He was the first on the scene.

675
00:53:46.166 --> 00:53:47.083
Get rid of him.

676
00:53:47.166 --> 00:53:49.458
A known perpetrator lies dead in there.

677
00:53:49.541 --> 00:53:51.875
-Don't go in.
-Get him out of there!

678
00:53:51.958 --> 00:53:54.583
Don't go in there. Harry.
Leave it. damn it.

679
00:53:55.166 --> 00:53:56.166
Harry...

680
00:54:57.458 --> 00:54:59.000
I'm sorry. Harry.

681
00:55:00.875 --> 00:55:02.250
I was too late.

682
00:57:04.375 --> 00:57:05.666
Open your eyes.

683
00:57:07.125 --> 00:57:09.541
It is a simple pattern.

684
00:57:11.708 --> 00:57:13.750
A red guiding star.

685
00:57:16.750 --> 00:57:19.083
A five-pointed devil's cross

686
00:57:20.083 --> 00:57:21.791
shows you the way.

687
00:57:29.041 --> 00:57:30.375
IN THIS SEASON

688
00:57:30.458 --> 00:57:33.875
It was hard with Ellen.
but you have to keep going.

689
00:57:33.958 --> 00:57:36.166
I can't cover for you all the time.

690
00:57:36.250 --> 00:57:38.750
If I let you
against Waaler.

691
00:57:38.833 --> 00:57:40.333
then you do it alone.

692
00:57:42.916 --> 00:57:46.375
Harry. a murder.
I need you at work. sober.

693
00:57:46.458 --> 00:57:47.416
Police.

694
00:57:47.500 --> 00:57:51.166
Lisbeth has disappeared.
The premiere is in eleven days.

695
00:57:51.958 --> 00:57:55.000
You didn't get any further?

696
00:57:55.083 --> 00:57:57.000
The best people are working on the case.

697
00:57:57.083 --> 00:57:58.750
This is for us.

698
00:57:58.833 --> 00:58:02.125
He wants us to know.
He wants to be admired.

699
00:58:02.208 --> 00:58:04.541
At the same time. he gives us
nothing tangible.

700
00:58:14.708 --> 00:58:18.250
What if I were to
join your project?

701
00:58:18.333 --> 00:58:21.750
You carry out a mission.
alone. no questions asked.

702
00:58:21.833 --> 00:58:23.708
You have to burn bridges.

703
00:58:23.791 --> 00:58:26.291
That's what we do. We'll take out the garbage.

704
00:58:26.916 --> 00:58:29.666
Come on. I'll show you the way.

705
00:58:32.500 --> 00:58:37.000
BASED ON THE NOVEL
THE FIFTH SIGN BY JO NESBØ

706
00:59:53.625 --> 00:59:55.541
Subtitle by: Carina Chadwick
